text: Input/Output Data The Input/Output data is the type of data that an agent expects and delivers. The agent expects GTPRecollectionRequestUDR and produces GTPRecollectionResponseUDR. Meta Information Model For information about the MIM and a list of the general MIM parameters, see Administration and Management in Legacy Desktop . Publishes MIM Value Description MIM Value Description NE Host (String) This MIM value contains the IP address of the connected network element. NE Port (Int) This MIM value contains the port of the connected network element. Requests in queue (Int) This MIM value contains the number of queued requests to the connected network element. Accesses The agent does not access any MIM parameters.
title: GTP' LGU ReCollection Agent Input/Output Data and MIM - MediationZone Documentation 9.4 - InfoZone
